<emphasis box="[199,357,1911,1936]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="142">Erebia manto</emphasis>
(Denis &amp; Schiffermüller, 1775)
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="143" pageId="14" pageNumber="142" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1911,2008]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1437,151,470]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="143" pageId="14" pageNumber="142">
—This European endemic has rarely been recorded in the Balkans, and is known only from Mt. Vlašić and Mt. Trebević in 
<collectingCountry box="[966,1044,1947,1972]" name="Bosnia and Herzegovina" pageId="14" pageNumber="142">Bosnia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[1065,1206,1947,1972]" pageId="14" pageNumber="142" refId="ref10550" refString="Rebel, H. (1904) Studien uber die Lepidopterenfauna der Balkanlander, II Teil Bosnien und Hercegovina. Annalen des k. k. Naturhistorischen Hofmuseum, 19, 97 - 337." type="journal article">Rebel 1904</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[1224,1371,1947,1972]" pageId="14" pageNumber="142" refId="ref11252" refString="Sijaric, R. (1982) Sastav populacija Rhopalocera (Lepidoptera) u ekosistemima planine Vlasic. Glasnik Zemaljskog Muzeja, P. N., New Series, 21, 163 - 172." type="journal article">Sijarić 1982</bibRefCitation>
). For 
<collectingCountry box="[151,288,1984,2008]" name="Serbia" pageId="14" pageNumber="142">Montenegro</collectingCountry>
it was recorded by 
<bibRefCitation box="[518,677,1983,2008]" pageId="14" pageNumber="142" refId="ref9367" refString="Kocak, A. O. (1989) On the butterflies of Yugoslavia (Lepidoptera). Centre for Entomological Studies, Priamus, 5 (1 / 2), 3 - 22." type="journal article">Koçak (1989)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[691,942,1983,2008]" pageId="14" pageNumber="142" refId="ref9007" refString="Jaksic, P. &amp; Pesic, B. (1995) The distribution of certain Erebia species in Serbia (Lepidoptera, Satyridae). [Rasprostranjenje nekih Erebia vrsta u Srbiji (Lepidoptera, Satyridae)]. Univerzitetska misao, 2 (1), 23 - 26." type="journal article">Jakšić &amp; Pešić (1995)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation box="[1001,1170,1983,2008]" pageId="14" pageNumber="142" refId="ref8940" refString="Jaksic, P. (2003 b) Fauna leptira (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae, Hesperioidea i Papilionoidea) metohijskih Prokletija. In: Amidzic, L., Jankovic, M. M. &amp; Jaksic, P. (Eds.), Metohijske Prokletije, prirodna i kulturna bastina. Zavod za zastitu prirode Srbije, Beograd, pp. 234 - 261." type="book chapter">Jakšić (2003b)</bibRefCitation>
. More precisely, it was observed in two localities in the Prokletije mountain range, namely Čakor pass based on one male specimen collected on 
<date box="[296,455,187,215]" pageId="15" pageNumber="143" value="1978-07-13">July 13th 1978</date>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[471,611,190,215]" pageId="15" pageNumber="143" refId="ref9367" refString="Kocak, A. O. (1989) On the butterflies of Yugoslavia (Lepidoptera). Centre for Entomological Studies, Priamus, 5 (1 / 2), 3 - 22." type="journal article">Koçak 1989</bibRefCitation>
) and another male on 
<date box="[867,1026,187,215]" pageId="15" pageNumber="143" value="1988-07-18">July 18th 1988</date>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[1041,1274,190,215]" pageId="15" pageNumber="143" refId="ref9007" refString="Jaksic, P. &amp; Pesic, B. (1995) The distribution of certain Erebia species in Serbia (Lepidoptera, Satyridae). [Rasprostranjenje nekih Erebia vrsta u Srbiji (Lepidoptera, Satyridae)]. Univerzitetska misao, 2 (1), 23 - 26." type="journal article">Jakšić &amp; Pešić 1995</bibRefCitation>
) and from the Karanfili massif, near Gusinje (
<bibRefCitation box="[500,652,226,251]" pageId="15" pageNumber="143" refId="ref8940" refString="Jaksic, P. (2003 b) Fauna leptira (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae, Hesperioidea i Papilionoidea) metohijskih Prokletija. In: Amidzic, L., Jankovic, M. M. &amp; Jaksic, P. (Eds.), Metohijske Prokletije, prirodna i kulturna bastina. Zavod za zastitu prirode Srbije, Beograd, pp. 234 - 261." type="book chapter">Jakšić 2003b</bibRefCitation>
). The species has been reported for the fauna of 
<collectingCountry box="[1187,1259,226,251]" name="Serbia" pageId="15" pageNumber="143">Serbia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation pageId="15" pageNumber="143" refId="ref9007" refString="Jaksic, P. &amp; Pesic, B. (1995) The distribution of certain Erebia species in Serbia (Lepidoptera, Satyridae). [Rasprostranjenje nekih Erebia vrsta u Srbiji (Lepidoptera, Satyridae)]. Univerzitetska misao, 2 (1), 23 - 26." type="journal article">Jakšić &amp; Pešić 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[224,374,262,287]" pageId="15" pageNumber="143" refId="ref8940" refString="Jaksic, P. (2003 b) Fauna leptira (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae, Hesperioidea i Papilionoidea) metohijskih Prokletija. In: Amidzic, L., Jankovic, M. M. &amp; Jaksic, P. (Eds.), Metohijske Prokletije, prirodna i kulturna bastina. Zavod za zastitu prirode Srbije, Beograd, pp. 234 - 261." type="book chapter">Jakšić 2003b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[389,592,262,287]" pageId="15" pageNumber="143" refId="ref9095" refString="Jaksic, P., Nahirnic, A. &amp; Petrovic, S. (2013) Compendium of Serbian Butterflies with vernacular names. Bulletin of the Natural History Museum, 6, 75 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.5937 / bnhmb 1306075 J" type="journal article">
Jakšić 
<emphasis box="[466,525,262,287]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="143">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
) since the eastern ranges of Mt. Čakor were within the boundaries of the Federal Republic of 
<collectingCountry box="[386,504,298,323]" name="Slovenia" pageId="15" pageNumber="143">Jugoslavia</collectingCountry>
in 1995, when the paper was published. However, currently Čakor pass is within Montenegrin territory. The author along with Martin Gascoigne-Pees visited Čakor pass on 
<date box="[1171,1329,333,362]" pageId="15" pageNumber="143" value="2017-07-14">July 14th 2017</date>
, however the species was not observed. Several entomologists have also visited this mountain pass, but have not reported 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Erebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manto">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="143">E. manto</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Weiss 1975; Floriani &amp; Saldaitis pers. comm.) The status of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[924,1026,410,433]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Erebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="143" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manto">
<emphasis box="[924,1026,410,433]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="143">E. manto</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Prokletije range has yet to be confirmed, since there are no photographic records and the author is not aware of any preserved specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
